        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 4:22PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Butler, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Knoxville, Roberta, Nakomis, Reynolds, Lee Pope, Horns, Potterville,
Butler, Hicks, and Fort Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
